Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the 
@linguine{180%g}.

Halve the @lemon{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a 
#garlic press{}). Slice the @sugar snap peas{80%g} in half lengthways.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. 
Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked 
through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its 
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, add the linguine to the pan of boiling water and 
bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is 
cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} 
and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir the 
sugar snap peas, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the 
same pan. Squeeze in some lemon juice and add the @water for the sauce{100%ml}, 
then stir to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, mix in half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, then 
lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once thickened, add the cooked pasta to the creamy sauce. Toss together to coat 
well. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if needed.

Share the creamy chicken linguine between your #bowls{}. Top with a sprinkling of 
the remaining @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Enjoy!